												<div class="description author withsidebar">
													<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/rosieschaap/">Rosie Schaap</a></h6>
													Rosie Schaap is the author of <em>Drinking with Men: A Memoir</em> and <em>Becoming a Sommelier</em>. She was a columnist for <em>The New York Times Magazine</em>, and has also contributed to the paper’s book review, dining, opinion, sports, and travel sections; <em>This American Life</em>; <em>Food & Wine</em>; <em>Marie Claire</em>; <em>Saveur</em>; <em>Travel + Leisure</em>; and many essay anthologies. She was previously employed as a community organizer and a manager of homeless shelters. A native New Yorker, she lives in Glenarm, Northern Ireland.																									</div>
											</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
										</div>

